McMAHON, Michael E. - Biographical Information


















McMAHON, Michael E., (1957 - )




Collection of the U.S. House of Representatives 

McMAHON, Michael E., a Representative from New York; born in Staten Island, Richmond 

County, N.Y., September 12, 1957; graduated from Monsignor Farrell High School, 

Staten Island, N.Y.; B.A., New York University, New York, N.Y., 1980; A.A. 

Heidelberg U., Heidelberg, Germany, 1983; J.D. New York University Law School, 

New York, N.Y., 1985; lawyer, private practice; member, New York city council, 

2002-2008; elected as a Democrat to the One Hundred Eleventh Congress (January 

3, 2009-January 3, 2011); unsuccessful candidate for reelection to the One 

Hundred Twelfth Congress in 2010; Staten Island, Richmond County, N.Y. district 

attorney, 2015-present.













Michael E. McMahon Esq. | Miller & Gaudio PC | 














































